                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>What is the definition of design?</span></strong></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Designing is a method or art of creating a prototype or specification for the creation of an object, system, or product.</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Designing might take the form of a sketch or a wireframe created with design tools such as a pencil and a sketch pen on paper, as well as computer software. Photoshop, Illustrator, Indesign, Coral Draw, pencil, sketch, and so on.</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>There are various types of design that are employed in the development of different products:</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Web design</span></strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>&nbsp;is a term used to describe the process of creating a design for a web application.</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Graphic design</span></strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>&nbsp;is used to create graphics for printing, media, and products, among other things.</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Animation Design</span></strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>&nbsp;is the process of making animations, visuals, and videos, among other things.</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Inside design</span></strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>&nbsp;is a term used to describe the process of designing the interior of a home, a hotel, or an office.</span></p>
                <p style='margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:107%;font-size:15px;font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";text-align:justify;'><strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>Fashion design</span></strong><span style='font-size:19px;line-height:107%;font-family:"Times New Roman","serif";'>&nbsp;is the process of creating gowns, garments, and footwear, among other things.</span></p>

